<subSubSection id="1D7DF6D514CF1EECC228E31A917B9F5B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="28C0401694A0B1371DD28236E99AD056" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="65148D2B243B2AA746744B77B8B6E9C4" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Portugal (
<bibRefCitation id="5BBDC358E8CC2FF34B58DF33CD59A509" author="Luna de Carvalho, E" journalOrPublisher="Memorias e Estudos do Museu Zoologico da Universidade de Coimbra" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 13" refId="B67" refString="Luna de Carvalho, E, 1960. Contribuicao para o conhecimento dos estrepsipteros de Portugal (lV Nota). Memorias e Estudos do Museu Zoologico da Universidade de Coimbra 263: 1 - 13" title="Contribuicao para o conhecimento dos estrepsipteros de Portugal (lV Nota)." volume="263" year="1960">Luna de Carvalho 1960</bibRefCitation>
); Palearctic (
<bibRefCitation id="D18D032BF46D1F80EEB5945A73B40F5B" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/syen.12460" author="Benda, D" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Entomology" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="252 - 265" refId="B4" refString="Benda, D, Votypkova, K, Nakase, Y, Straka, J, 2021. Unexpected cryptic species diversity of parasites of the family Xenidae (Strepsiptera) with a constant diversification rate over time. Systematic Entomology 46: 252 - 265, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/syen.12460" title="Unexpected cryptic species diversity of parasites of the family Xenidae (Strepsiptera) with a constant diversification rate over time." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/syen.12460" volume="46" year="2021">Benda et al. 2021</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A44269B015BB764B5E842FABDA8F0289" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="E41FA07F51CA1ADE7026EEEE114591FB" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E7705453710B4066F6B09F79BEA3D6A0" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
This species corresponds to a lineage widely distributed from Portugal to Mongolia (
<bibRefCitation id="4C0E42FAC7ECEF62260C6472347753E7" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/syen.12460" author="Benda, D" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Entomology" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="252 - 265" refId="B4" refString="Benda, D, Votypkova, K, Nakase, Y, Straka, J, 2021. Unexpected cryptic species diversity of parasites of the family Xenidae (Strepsiptera) with a constant diversification rate over time. Systematic Entomology 46: 252 - 265, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/syen.12460" title="Unexpected cryptic species diversity of parasites of the family Xenidae (Strepsiptera) with a constant diversification rate over time." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/syen.12460" volume="46" year="2021">Benda et al. 2021</bibRefCitation>
). Although its phylogenetic position is still unclear, it is provisionally included into 
<taxonomicName id="79558E8A593121FCECCF6445AC7C50C6" authority="Benda, Pohl, Nakase, Beutel &amp; Straka, 2022" authorityName="Benda &amp; Pohl &amp; Nakase &amp; Beutel &amp; Straka" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Xenidae" genus="Deltoxenos" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Deltoxenos" order="Strepsiptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="991512BCEC51C490574D268E501FA6F7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Deltoxenos</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gen. nov. here based on morphology.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
